WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:01.434
Previously, on Chesapeake Shores...

00:01.440 --> 00:02.832
What happened between you and Bree?

00:02.867 --> 00:04.767
Bree isn't very good at keeping secrets.

00:04.773 --> 00:06.215
I saw Danielle come out of a restaurant

00:06.221 --> 00:08.047
with some guy. They seemed close.

00:08.053 --> 00:09.309
I don't want to see you get hurt.

00:09.315 --> 00:11.240
You assume she's cheating on me,

00:11.275 --> 00:12.570
and you don't want me to be hurt?

00:12.576 --> 00:14.410
David's inviting us to
Maine to meet his parents!

00:14.445 --> 00:16.122
Do you ever think about what would've

00:16.128 --> 00:17.689
happened if I had come
back from New York?

00:17.695 --> 00:19.595
Something tells me I'd
still be here with you.

00:19.601 --> 00:21.695
Robin! What brings you back here?

00:21.701 --> 00:23.402
They're gonna renew their vows.

00:23.408 --> 00:26.053
Just seems that after 30
years of trying harder...

00:26.059 --> 00:28.126
Thanks for the support, Mick.

00:34.347 --> 00:35.380
Whoo!

00:35.415 --> 00:36.714
Grapevine to the right...

00:36.750 --> 00:38.515
Heel! Grapevine to the left...

00:38.521 --> 00:40.351
Heel! And heel! And... kick.

00:40.689 --> 00:41.955
Ta-dah!

00:41.961 --> 00:43.087
Whoo!

00:43.123 --> 00:44.639
We end on the right foot.

00:44.645 --> 00:46.516
Oops! My other right foot. Heh.

00:47.090 --> 00:48.356
Maybe Mom wants to try.

00:48.362 --> 00:49.494
Yeah! Come on!

00:49.529 --> 00:51.329
Uh, girls, actually,
we need to get going,

00:51.364 --> 00:52.697
or you're going to be
late for gymnastics.

00:52.732 --> 00:53.943
Boo!

00:53.949 --> 00:55.600
Okay.

00:55.635 --> 00:57.101
You know, one of these days,

00:57.137 --> 00:59.504
you're gonna run out of excuses,

00:59.539 --> 01:01.172
and I'm gonna teach you
how to line dance.

01:01.207 --> 01:04.342
Uh, no, but, see, I
have years of excuses

01:04.376 --> 01:05.543
all stocked up.

01:07.197 --> 01:09.881
So, Bree's manuscript
getting any easier to read?

01:09.916 --> 01:12.250
Uh, it's not so bad for me,

01:12.285 --> 01:15.170
but I think it's going to be
hard for some of the family.

01:15.176 --> 01:16.421
Anything about me?

01:16.456 --> 01:17.789
There is a part

01:17.824 --> 01:19.724
about a dashing country line dancer.

01:19.759 --> 01:21.559
Who can't tell his left
foot from his right?

01:21.594 --> 01:24.312
But his girlfriend's
daughters love him anyways.

01:25.328 --> 01:27.465
I can't believe your
break is over already.

01:27.500 --> 01:29.532
Well, this time, I won't
be gone for so long.

01:29.538 --> 01:31.636
Three weeks, and I'll be
touring the mid-Atlantic,

01:31.671 --> 01:33.237
so I'll be close to home for a month.

01:33.273 --> 01:35.740
Mm. It's gonna be tough sharing you.

01:35.775 --> 01:37.275
You could always come with me.

01:37.848 --> 01:40.611
Ah, Trace, I told you, I'm no groupie.

01:40.647 --> 01:43.147
Groupie? I was thinking roadie.

01:43.183 --> 01:44.549
How are you at heavy lifting?

01:44.584 --> 01:45.717
I'm very strong.

01:45.752 --> 01:47.752
Let me see. You are strong.

01:47.787 --> 01:50.588
Actually, I already have a second job.

01:50.623 --> 01:53.791
I am now the new night
manager over at Jess's B&B

01:53.827 --> 01:54.992
while she's out of town with Bree.

01:55.028 --> 01:56.461
That should be fun for the girls,

01:56.496 --> 01:58.496
- kind of like a sleepover.
- Yeah, you should come by.

01:58.531 --> 02:00.941
Say goodnight to the
girls, read them a story.

02:02.410 --> 02:04.644
I mean, if you... if you...
if you want to do that.

02:04.650 --> 02:07.071
- You don't have to.
- No, no. No. It sounds like fun.

02:07.216 --> 02:09.354
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

02:09.691 --> 02:11.491
I mean, it's a lot of work.

02:11.497 --> 02:12.596
Abby...

02:12.602 --> 02:14.512
I only have three more days at home,

02:14.518 --> 02:16.223
and I want to spend every minute of it

02:16.258 --> 02:18.449
with you, Carrie, and Caitlyn.

02:20.013 --> 02:21.210
Come on.

02:21.216 --> 02:22.920
What? No, no, no!

02:22.956 --> 02:25.123
I have a headache!
And I need to go to work,

02:25.158 --> 02:26.459
and I have to wash my hair...

02:26.465 --> 02:28.259
Abby, just dance with us, okay?

02:30.063 --> 02:31.362
Let's show her how it's done.

02:31.397 --> 02:33.698
Ready? One, two, three!

02:33.733 --> 02:34.966
Heel, heel,

02:35.001 --> 02:37.335
toe, toe, toe-toe-toe...

02:37.370 --> 02:40.104
Slap, slap, grapevine to the right...

02:41.574 --> 02:42.840
Grapevine to the left...

02:42.876 --> 02:45.109
Heel... and heel... and kick!

